Modifications
-------------
The original articles have been modified for use as a Markdown note corpus:

  - Converted from Wikipedia HTML/wikitext to Obsidian-flavored Markdown.
  - Links between articles included in this corpus were rewritten as
    `[[wikilinks]]`; links to articles outside the corpus were reduced to
    plain text.
  - Infoboxes, reference lists, citations, and navigation chrome were removed.
  - Content was truncated/selected for evaluation purposes.

These are adaptations within the meaning of CC BY-SA 4.0. No endorsement by
Wikipedia or its contributors is implied.

Authorship
----------
Each article was authored by Wikipedia contributors. The complete author list
and edit history for any article is available from its revision permalink in
the table below (the "oldid" URL shows the exact pinned version and its
"View history" lists all contributors).

Attributed articles
--------------------
Each row records the source article, the exact revision the snapshot was pinned
to, and the local file it produced. Rows are appended by the corpus build
script as articles are fetched, so this table stays complete and in sync with
the committed snapshot.

Format (tab- or pipe-separated):

  Local file | Article title | Language | Source (revision permalink)

Example (illustrative; replaced by real rows at build time):

  string-instruments/violin.md | Violin | en | https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Violin&oldid=<REVID>

